linhello (0.6.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Update path: on Fedora, `linhello update` now tracks the Copr repository via
    dnf (auto-enabling it if missing) instead of rebuilding from a signed tag —
    equivalent to `dnf upgrade --refresh linhello`, keeping a Fedora install
    rpm-managed. Other distros keep the signed-tag source rebuild.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 12:30:00 -0400

linhello (0.6.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Profiles: create named profiles to enroll into — `linhello enroll --user NAME`
    makes a separate profile and a new `--name "Label"` sets its display name; the
    setup TUI Profiles screen's `a` key types a new profile name and targets it.
  * TUI fix: the Profiles-screen delete prompt/result no longer overflow the fixed
    footer — they go to the scrollable Activity panel, and long footer status is
    ellipsis-clipped to one line.
  * Camera auto-brightness: after AE warmup the capture path drives the camera
    brightness control so the face lands near mid-scale, fixing chronically dark
    exposure (e.g. ~44 → ~110 luma) that fed the recognizer a too-dark face.
  * TUI: vertical scroll sliders on the Activity and Host-check boxes, plus mouse
    support (wheel scrolls the box under the cursor; drag the slider thumb).
  * New `linhello update-check`: reports whether a newer release is available
    (Copr/dnf on Fedora, signed git tags elsewhere); the setup TUI shows an
    update-available notice with the right upgrade command for how it was installed.
  * Framing guidance fixes: lower the too-dark floor so a well-lit face is no longer
    told "More light"; only flag backlighting when the face itself is dim; and
    correct the inverted chin/pitch advice (chin-up now says "Lower your chin").

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 11:00:00 -0400

linhello (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Recover face auth after suspend/resume. UVC webcams commonly fail to resume
    from USB suspend, leaving the camera present but wedged; this manifested as
    the greeter hanging on "Looking for your face…" with no camera engaging,
    surviving reboots until the camera power-cycled. Fixed three ways: bound the
    previously-unbounded camera enumeration/resolution with a deadline so a frozen
    camera can never hang the PAM stack (it degrades to the password in seconds);
    log the screen-unlock Verify outcome + timing (it was silent, making the
    failure undiagnosable); and add a systemd system-sleep hook that try-restarts
    the daemon on resume to re-open the camera (the camera-refresh udev rule only
    fires on re-enumeration, which a resume often skips).
  * Fix face unlock failing with "Device or resource busy": the KDE lock screen
    runs two PAM stacks at once (kde + kde-fingerprint), so two captures opened
    the camera simultaneously and the loser got EBUSY. Camera I/O is now
    serialised process-wide so concurrent verifies queue instead of colliding.
  * Detect a hardware camera privacy switch (V4L2_CID_PRIVACY): when blocked, the
    sensor returns blank frames that previously surfaced as a baffling "no face
    detected" no reboot could fix. Capture now fails fast with a clear "camera
    privacy switch is ON — toggle the camera-privacy key (e.g. Fn+F10)" message,
    and doctor flags it on the RGB/IR rows.
  * Tell the user at the greeter/lock screen WHY face unlock didn't run (privacy
    switch on / no camera) instead of a silent password fall-through; auto
    re-engage once the camera is unblocked.
  * Stronger liveness/anti-spoofing: (a) the ML anti-spoof is median-aggregated
    across a short capture burst so one noisy frame no longer false-rejects a live
    user, while a real photo/screen still rejects (LINHELLO_ANTISPOOF_FRAMES);
    (b) a new enrollment-calibrated active-IR gate records the live user's own IR
    signature — face/bg ratio, corneal glint, and a depth/curvature cue (center vs
    edge IR brightness; a 3-D face is center-bright, a flat photo/screen uniform) —
    and requires the live IR to match it, catching printed photos AND glossy
    screens without the absolute thresholds that false-rejected live users before.
    Additive to ML, fail-closed, opt-in via re-enrollment (LINHELLO_IR_GATE=0 to
    disable); legacy profiles unaffected until re-enrolled.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 20:00:00 -0400

linhello (0.4.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * `linhello update`: build the Arch native package as an unprivileged user
    instead of as root (makepkg refuses to run as root). When updating from the
    root-owned managed clone the native build failed and the updater silently
    fell back to a from-source install; it now builds as the checkout owner (or
    the sudo invoker) in a user-owned build dir, and surfaces native-build
    failures rather than degrading to source. Arch-only path; rpm/deb unchanged.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:00:00 -0400

linhello (0.4.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Plasma 6 / KDE lock screen + login fixes: the daemon classifies the
    `plasmalogin` greeter (and -greeter/-autologin) as login/unlock; the KDE lock
    screen is wired on Debian (not just Arch); `setup`/`pam enable` and the TUI
    wizard add the user to the `linhello` group so the user-run greeter can reach
    the daemon socket.
  * Close a camera cgroup device boot-race with a udev rule + oneshot that
    refreshes the daemon's device access once the webcam enumerates; reload udev
    rules on install so it takes effect without a reboot.
  * TUI wizard parity with `linhello setup`: install the reseal hook, add group
    membership unconditionally, offer a recovery passphrase, and confirm the
    login password (typed twice) before sealing.

