linhello (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Self-healing TPM binding on GRUB systems. A firmware/dbx update (e.g. via
    fwupd) moves PCR 7 and previously broke face unlock until a re-enroll. The
    template key is now sealed under a PolicyAuthorize policy signed by a
    per-host key, and the new PCR-7 state is re-signed automatically on the
    first unlock after the change — while Secure Boot stays enabled — so face
    unlock survives firmware updates with no re-enrollment.
  * Boot mode is detected automatically: UKI keeps systemd's signed PCR-11
    policy; GRUB uses linhello's own PCR-7 signer.
  * New dedicated recovery passphrase (separate from the login password), the
    manual backstop for cases the automatic heal can't cover (Secure Boot off,
    TPM cleared, disk moved): `linhello set-recovery` / `linhello recover`.
  * Validated the previously-pending PolicyAuthorize TPM path on real hardware.
  * Fingerprint as a standalone secure-tier unlock method (via fprintd). On
    RGB-only machines (no IR) it's the secure default — unlocking screen, login,
    and sudo — while RGB-only face stays available as a convenience option.
    `method = fingerprint` suppresses the face prompt; `pam_fprintd` is wired
    per distro (pam-auth-update on Debian, authselect on Fedora, guided on Arch).
    New `linhello fingerprint {status,enable,disable,add}`, named fingerprints,
    duplicate detection, and a fingerprint step in `setup` and the TUI.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 11:30:00 -0400

